  "problemId": "3",
  "title": "Library Access Constraints",
  "briefparagraph": "Students face limited access to library resources, especially during peak exam times and evenings.",
  "description": "Campus libraries often have restricted hours, limited seating, and insufficient study materials for large student populations. Students are unable to access reference books or quiet study spaces during late hours or exam periods, affecting their preparation and academic performance.\n\nWe propose a smart library management system with (1) extended hours monitoring using secure access, (2) real-time seat availability tracking, (3) automated book reservation and delivery, (4) AI-based recommendations for study resources, and (5) analytics for library administration to plan capacity and acquisitions.",
